00:05:56.280 --> 00:05:58.230
Meaning, when someone
starts watching your video,

00:05:58.230 --> 00:06:00.420
let's say it's a 60-second Short,

00:06:00.420 --> 00:06:02.820
which is the max duration you could do,

00:06:02.820 --> 00:06:04.290
you want them to watch all of it.

00:06:04.290 --> 00:06:07.470
Or maybe it's a shorter Short
and it's 10 seconds long.

00:06:07.470 --> 00:06:10.170
You want them to watch
that over and over again

00:06:10.170 --> 00:06:12.660
and kinda spike that
average view duration.

00:06:12.660 --> 00:06:14.280
Now, I have a method that I use

00:06:14.280 --> 00:06:15.930
that is gonna help you guys as well,

00:06:15.930 --> 00:06:18.270
and this is called the loop method.

00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:19.680
Now, you've probably seen this before

00:06:19.680 --> 00:06:21.870
when you're watching
a video and the ending

00:06:21.870 --> 00:06:24.150
actually synchronizes with the beginning.

00:06:24.150 --> 00:06:25.440
Now, if you're going to do this,

00:06:25.440 --> 00:06:27.180
you really need to start thinking back

00:06:27.180 --> 00:06:28.440
during the scripting phase,

00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:31.050
